//@version=6
// ============================================================
// KSHANA SYSTEM STRATEGY — v2 — 2026-07-12   ★ ATR-EQUAL-RISK POSITION SIZING ★
// Complete walk-forward-validated system. For PAPER forward-testing + live execution via webhook.
// ============================================================
// Put this on a 5m chart of ONE future (NQ, ES, YM, RTY, CL, GC, NG). Auto-detects the instrument.
// It trades the validated system:
//   1. ENTRY: 5m+15m aligned crossing (mirror_dir direction), enter next bar.
//   2. EXIT: per-instrument personality — FLIP (hold to opposite signal) for trend-catchers
//      (NQ/YM/RTY/CL), ATR-TRAIL for grinders (NG=5, GC=8, ES=8).
//   3. SESSION: force-flat 4:45PM ET, no entries 4:45-6:00PM, resume 6:00PM.
//   (Regime gate REMOVED 2026-07-09: near-wash system-wide, hurt indices, clashed with style.)
// Instrument verdict: TRADE NQ/GC/CL/YM (real edge). ES/NG/RTY marginal. SI dropped (loser).
// ============================================================
// WEBHOOK EXECUTION → NinjaTrader via CrossTrade (recommended path):
//   PIPELINE: TradingView (this strategy fires alert) -> CrossTrade (bridge) -> NinjaTrader 8 desktop.
//   NinjaTrader setup: Tools>Import>NinjaScript Add-On (CrossTrade XT add-on); Tools>Options>ATI = ON;
//     restart; open XT add-on, log in (green = connected). NT8 needs a data feed active (sim is fine).
//   TradingView: 2FA MUST be enabled (else webhooks silently fail).
//   THIS STRATEGY: set account name (default Sim101 - use SIM FIRST), contracts (default 1), keep
//     Strategy Sync ON. It emits CrossTrade commands: PLACE buy/sell on entries/flips, FLATTEN on exits.
//   ★★ TWO SEPARATE CREDENTIALS, TWO DIFFERENT PLACES (both from crosstrade.io > My Account):
//      1. SECRET KEY -> paste into this strategy's "CrossTrade SECRET KEY" input (goes IN the message)
//      2. WEBHOOK URL -> paste into the TradingView alert's NOTIFICATIONS tab (the address to send to)
//      Getting these backwards is the #1 setup failure. Key = in message. URL = in Notifications.
//   CREATE THE ALERT: right-click chart > Add alert > Condition = THIS STRATEGY >
//     "Any alert() function call" > "Once Per Bar Close" > Message = leave {{alert_message}} default >
//     Notifications tab: check Webhook, paste your CrossTrade webhook URL > Create.
//   TEST FIRST: use CrossTrade's Webhook Trader to send a manual order to Sim101 and confirm it fills
//     in NinjaTrader BEFORE arming the alert. Then: sim (multiple sessions) -> micro-live -> scale.
//   NOTE: 5m bar-close timing means ~30s webhook latency is invisible (next bar is 5min away).
//   RISK: the ATR trail (GC/NG/ES) is computed IN this script — it only fires when the bar closes and
//   the alert sends. A dropped connection = the trail won't exit. Strategy Sync mitigates; sim-test it.
// ============================================================
// ★★★ WHAT'S NEW IN v2: ATR-EQUAL-RISK POSITION SIZING ★★★
// v1 traded 1 contract of everything. That was NEVER equal risk. Measured $ risk per 1 ATR move,
// per ONE contract, on the validated data:
//        NQ $284  |  GC $254  |  CL $97  |  YM $66  |  NG $30
// One NQ contract carried ~9x the risk of one NG contract. The "5-instrument portfolio" was really
// an NQ bet with four decorations — you were only collecting a fraction of the diversification.
// v2 sizes each trade so every instrument risks the SAME dollars per ATR.
//
// VALIDATED (8wk, 5 futures, walk-forward, and controlled against pure leverage):
//     fixed 1.00 contract          ret/DD 2.07   OOS 2.07 / 0.94
//     fixed 2.73 contracts         ret/DD 2.07   OOS 0.94    <- pure leverage does NOTHING
//     fixed 3.00 contracts         ret/DD 2.07   OOS 0.94    <- still nothing
//     ATR-EQUAL-RISK (same 2.73 avg size)  ret/DD 4.05   OOS 2.82   <- REAL
//   Same signals, same trades, same average size. Max drawdown -101,484 -> -59,522 (-41%) AND more
//   money. It is NOT leverage (leverage is provably inert above). It survives OUT-OF-SAMPLE.
//   This is worth more than every entry/exit filter we tested combined (all 5 of those died OOS).
//
// ★ NEVER HARDCODE POINT VALUES. This script uses syminfo.pointvalue exclusively.
//   (The SI bug: hardcoded $50 vs the real $5,000 = 100x error that made a -$47,600 loser look
//    like breakeven for the ENTIRE project. TV's live pointvalue is the only truth.)
//   Bonus: this makes MICRO CONTRACTS WORK AUTOMATICALLY. On MNQ, syminfo.pointvalue = 2 (not 20),
//   so the same formula naturally sizes ~10x more contracts for the same dollar risk. No special case.
//
// ★ SET "Risk per trade" TO ~0.3-0.5% OF YOUR ACCOUNT.
//     $10,000 account  -> risk $30-50   (use MICROS: MNQ/MYM/MGC/MCL)
//     $50,000 account  -> risk $150-250
//     $180,000 account -> risk $600     (the size the backtest above was run at)
//   Too high a risk = the caps bind and you are just levering. Too low = size rounds to 0/1.
//   The table on the chart shows the computed size and the actual $ risk. WATCH IT.
//
// ★ WITH VARIABLE SIZE, STRATEGY SYNC IS NO LONGER OPTIONAL. A flip goes from (say) long 2 to
//   short 5 — NinjaTrader must trade 7. Keep Strategy Sync ON and SIM-TEST FLIPS before going live.
// ============================================================
// HONEST: ~5 walk-forward weeks + ~1 session live. Backtest is the base, not a promise.
// The sizing math is validated on the SAME 8 weeks as everything else. It is not a new edge —
// it is the SAME edge, collected properly.
// ============================================================
// ★ MARGIN: futures trade on margin, NOT full notional. Without margin_long/short set, TV demands
//   the FULL contract value (1 NQ = 29,000 x $20 = $580,000!) and silently REJECTS orders when
//   capital runs out — that is why 1M capital gave 19 trades and 2M gave 73. Real NQ margin is
//   ~$25k on $580k notional = ~4-5%. Setting 5% makes the backtest realistic at sane capital AND
//   makes it work on a $10k account with micros (1 MNQ = $58k notional x 5% = ~$2.9k margin).
//   ★ CAPITAL: at risk=$1200 this sizes 1-3 NQ contracts. 3 NQ = $1.74M notional = $87k margin at
//     5%. On $100k capital that is 87% margined on entry -> TV MARGIN-CALLS you and silently
//     liquidates part of the position (measured: 4 margin calls, 11 trades lost, count 73 -> 68).
//     $1M makes margin ~9% utilised so it never binds. THE BACKTEST CAPITAL DOES NOT AFFECT LIVE —
//     live sizing is set by risk_per_trade, and your broker holds the margin.
//     (For the $10k live account on MICROS: 1 MNQ = $58k notional x 5% = ~$2.9k margin. Fine.)
strategy("KSHANA System Strategy v2", overlay=true, initial_capital=1000000,
   margin_long=5, margin_short=5,
   default_qty_type=strategy.fixed, default_qty_value=1, pyramiding=0,
   commission_type=strategy.commission.cash_per_contract, commission_value=2.5,
   calc_on_every_tick=false, process_orders_on_close=true)

// ─── inputs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
string gI="Instrument (auto-detects from symbol; override if needed)"
string inst_ovr=input.string("AUTO","Instrument",options=["AUTO","NQ","ES","YM","RTY","CL","GC","NG","SI","ZB","ZN"],group=gI)
string gE="Engine"
int ss_len=input.int(13,"Line TEMA",group=gE)
int lr_len=input.int(25,"LR EMA",group=gE)
int v_len=input.int(50,"V EMA",group=gE)
int atr_len=input.int(14,"ATR",group=gE)
string wave_tf=input.timeframe("15","15m (WAVE) tf",group=gE)
string gX="Exit / Session"
bool use_trail=input.bool(true,"Use per-instrument trail (else flip only)",group=gX)
bool use_session=input.bool(true,"Force-flat 4:45PM, resume 6:00PM ET",group=gX)
string gD="Backtest window"
bool use_startdate=input.bool(true,"Only trade from start date onward",group=gD)
int start_date=input.time(timestamp("19 May 2026 00:00 -0400"),"Start date (validated window begin)",group=gD)
string gW="Webhook / Execution"
bool test_fire=input.bool(false,"★ TEST FIRE — force ONE real order now (turn OFF after)",group=gW,tooltip="Places a REAL long on the next 5m bar close, without waiting for a 5m+15m alignment. Because the CrossTrade command now rides on the ORDER (alert_message), this tests the EXACT production path: TradingView order fill -> alert -> CrossTrade -> NinjaTrader. It only fires when FLAT, so it fires once. The 16:45 session close will then close it, testing the CLOSEPOSITION path too. TURN IT OFF once you have seen the fill.")
bool use_alerts=input.bool(true,"(unused - orders always carry alert_message)",group=gW,tooltip="Kept for backwards compat. The CrossTrade command now rides on each ORDER via alert_message, so it fires whenever an order fires. Nothing to toggle.")
string gS="★ Position Sizing (ATR equal-risk)"
bool use_atr_size=input.bool(true,"ATR-EQUAL-RISK sizing (recommended)",group=gS,tooltip="ON = size each trade so a 1-ATR adverse move costs the same dollars on every instrument. This is the single highest-value change in the system (ret/DD 2.07 -> 4.05, and it holds out-of-sample). OFF = fixed contracts (v1 behaviour).")
float risk_per_trade=input.float(600.0,"Risk per trade ($ per 1 ATR)",minval=1.0,step=10,group=gS,tooltip="Dollar risk of a 1-ATR adverse move. SET THIS TO ~0.3-0.5% OF YOUR ACCOUNT. $10k acct -> $30-50 (use MICROS). $50k -> $150-250. $180k -> $600 (backtest size). The chart table shows the resulting contract size and true $ risk — watch it.")
int max_ct=input.int(20,"Max contracts (safety cap)",minval=1,group=gS,tooltip="SAFETY CEILING ONLY - it should almost NEVER bind. Set it high (20). If it binds, equal-risk is broken: cheap instruments (MYM/MCL/ZB) legitimately need 4-8 contracts at the same dollar risk that buys 1 MNQ. A LOW cap silently clips exactly those instruments and destroys the whole point. It exists only to stop a freak low-ATR print from blowing up the size.")
int min_ct=input.int(1,"Min contracts (floor)",minval=1,group=gS)
int fixed_ct=input.int(1,"Fixed contracts (used when ATR sizing is OFF)",minval=1,group=gS)
string ct_key=input.string("","★ CrossTrade SECRET KEY (paste here)",group=gW,tooltip="Your CrossTrade secret key, from the My Account page on crosstrade.io. THIS IS REQUIRED — without it every alert fails with 'Secret key missing, invalid, or inactive'. NOTE: this is SEPARATE from the Webhook URL, which goes in the alert's Notifications tab. Key = in the message. URL = in Notifications.")
string ct_account=input.string("Sim101","CrossTrade / NinjaTrader account name",group=gW,tooltip="The NinjaTrader account to trade. Use your sim account (e.g. Sim101) FIRST. Must match the account name shown in NinjaTrader's Accounts tab exactly.")
string ct_symbol=input.string("","Instrument override (blank = chart ticker like NQ1!)",group=gW,tooltip="Blank uses the chart's ticker (e.g. NQ1!). CrossTrade auto-converts NQ1! to the NinjaTrader contract (NQ 09-26). Only override to hard-code a contract for manual rollover control.")
bool ct_sync=input.bool(true,"Strategy Sync (recommended - self-corrects desyncs)",group=gW,tooltip="ON = CrossTrade compares the strategy's intended position vs NinjaTrader's actual position before executing, and corrects mismatches (protects against a dropped webhook stranding a position). Strongly recommended for this flip/trail strategy.")

tema(src,len)=>
    e1=ta.ema(src,len), e2=ta.ema(e1,len), e3=ta.ema(e2,len)
    3*e1-3*e2+e3

// AUTO-GENERATED 7-state magnitude tree (depth-8, 179 leaves) — EXACT 1:1.
// ~74% full-state match OOS. Outputs RATING (-7..+7) directly. Used for bar-coloring/display.
mirror_rating(v1, gLR, dgLR, gV, gLRV, stack) =>
    int _r = (v1 <= 0.001324 ? (gLR <= 0.098000 ? (gLRV <= -0.262845 ? (dgLR <= -0.052287 ? (gLR <= -0.099949 ? (gLRV <= -0.805693 ? (gLR <= -4.972056 ? 0 : (gLR <= -3.713768 ? -7 : -7)) : (gLR <= -2.576554 ? (dgLR <= -0.233652 ? -5 : 0) : (dgLR <= -0.109742 ? -7 : -7))) : (gLRV <= -0.719693 ? 0 : 0)) : (gLR <= -1.966946 ? (gLRV <= -2.484921 ? (dgLR <= 0.182269 ? -7 : 0) : (dgLR <= 0.023450 ? (gLRV <= -1.004653 ? -7 : 0) : (gLRV <= -1.615935 ? 0 : 0))) : (gLRV <= -0.723587 ? (gLR <= -0.195369 ? (dgLR <= 0.003591 ? -7 : -7) : (gLR <= -0.042693 ? 0 : 0)) : (gV <= -1.507691 ? (v1 <= -0.081287 ? 0 : 0) : (v1 <= -0.071685 ? -7 : 0))))) : (dgLR <= -0.040476 ? (gLRV <= 0.086850 ? (gLR <= -0.043386 ? (gLR <= -1.569474 ? (dgLR <= -0.217579 ? -5 : 0) : (v1 <= -0.329555 ? -7 : -5)) : 0) : (dgLR <= -1.450826 ? 0 : (dgLR <= -0.140464 ? (gLR <= -2.665313 ? -5 : -5) : (gLRV <= 0.415205 ? -5 : -5)))) : (gLR <= -1.116380 ? (gLR <= -1.832383 ? (gLRV <= 0.175357 ? (gLRV <= -0.084383 ? 0 : 0) : 0) : (gV <= -1.298587 ? (v1 <= -0.071070 ? -5 : 0) : (dgLR <= 0.028046 ? 0 : 0))) : (v1 <= -0.025244 ? (gLR <= -0.550250 ? (v1 <= -0.089331 ? -5 : 0) : (gLRV <= 0.703167 ? -5 : -5)) : (dgLR <= 0.040203 ? (gLR <= -0.623880 ? 0 : 0) : -5))))) : (gLR <= 0.630389 ? (gLRV <= 0.376392 ? (gLRV <= -0.039378 ? (gLR <= 0.139477 ? 0 : (gLRV <= -1.281409 ? 0 : (gLRV <= -0.168557 ? 0 : 0))) : (gLR <= 0.259479 ? (v1 <= -0.165676 ? (gLRV <= 0.091890 ? 0 : -3) : 0) : (dgLR <= -0.317468 ? 0 : (gLR <= 0.408250 ? 0 : 0)))) : (v1 <= -0.053303 ? (gLR <= 0.352859 ? (gLRV <= 1.920476 ? (gLRV <= 1.023609 ? -3 : -3) : -5) : (gV <= 1.717015 ? (gLR <= 0.495356 ? 0 : 0) : (gLRV <= 1.691899 ? -3 : -3))) : (gLR <= 0.326176 ? (gV <= 1.272220 ? 0 : 0) : (gLRV <= 0.919574 ? 0 : 0)))) : (gLRV <= 2.283147 ? (gLR <= 0.938614 ? (gLRV <= 1.469584 ? (gLRV <= 0.834272 ? (gLR <= 0.898899 ? 0 : 0) : (gLR <= 0.689811 ? 0 : 0)) : (dgLR <= -0.219943 ? (v1 <= -0.354501 ? -3 : -3) : 0)) : (gLRV <= 1.702368 ? (gLR <= 0.979319 ? (gLRV <= 0.773